_Pu’al_ Past Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_pu’al_ past tense]] follows the following conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|                | *Singular* |\<                              | *Plural* |\< |
| *First-Person* | זֻמַּנְתִּי<br>_zumanti_<br>I was invited | \<       | זֻמַּנּוּ<br>_zumannu_<br>We were invited | \< |
| *Second-Person* | זֻמַּנְתָּ <br>_zumanto_<br> You [male] were invited | זֻמַּנְתְּ <br>_zumant_<br> You [female] were invited  | זֻמַּנְתֶּם <br>_zumantem_<br> You [males] were invited  | זֻמַּנְתֶּן <br>_zumanten_<br> You [females] were invited |
| *Third-Person* | זֻמַּן <br>_zuman_<br> He was invited | זֻמְּנָה <br>_zumno_<br> She was invited  | זֻמְּנוּ <br>_zumnu_<br> They [male or female] were invited  | \< |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎ז, ‎מ, and ן above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
